						               													<description>Lands of Loot is a fantasy board game for 2- 6 players. The players assume the role of an aspiring adventurer who sets out on a journey to build their reputation. At the end of the game each player will have made a tale of heroic deeds, awful blunders, epic battles, and of course loot!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players start with creating a hero by drawing a combination of Folk and Class cards, then take turns rolling a 12 sided die and moving their meeple through a branching track. The game board itself is a map of the &amp;quot;Lands of Loot&amp;quot; and the track contains spaces that relate to their position on map.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The spaces can be events that cause the player to either gain or lose reputation points (RP)- sometimes paying the points to other players in the game. RP is represented by silver/gold coins and glass gems.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Some of the other spaces include monsters, which earn players RP based on their class, and loot chests which allow the player to draw from a limited deck of loot cards. When the loot deck runs out, loot can be taken from other players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Once every player reaches the end of the track, the reputation for each player totaled and each player is given a title based on their finishing RP. The player with the highest RP is declared the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
